<item>
            <title>[LU-16767] Allow JobID field widths </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16767</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Allow admins to specify a field width like &quot;&lt;tt&gt;%12p&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; for eg. the process name to truncate it below the 16-character maximum that the kernel imposes, and give more room to the other fields to fit into the JobID limit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It may also be possible to have a negative field width like &quot;&lt;tt&gt;%-8H&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to use the last 8 characters of the short hostname instead of the first 8 (if over 8 characters long).  This may have other issues, but can be useful in some cases, and would be up to the discretion of the admin.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
